      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just looking at some footage of the milky way and it just made me feel sick. like, everything we do, every single thing, is just a tiny blip of chemical reactions in a universe that's eventually just going to be cold and dead anyway. if it all ends in heat death and nothing we do leaves a mark, then what’s even the point of struggling through the day just to exist? it feels like we're all just performing a play for an empty theater.",
